The area contains various fossil sites containing traces of human occupation and evolution dating back some 3.3million years.

The site consists of eight protected areas that are among the richest in plant life worldwide, containing nearly 20% of Africa's total flora. Its scientific value is demonstrated by the presence of fire and radiation adaptivity in plants and seed dispersal by insects.
The park features soaring basaltic buttresses, incisive dramatic cutbacks, golden sandstone ramparts, rolling high-altitude grasslands, pristine steep-sided river valleys and rocky gorges.

data: Among the instruments of the Jesuit mission in Topaga it is found that vihuelas and discantes are different kind of instruments.
The tiple is mentioned for the first time in Popayan to designate a chordophone different from the guitar
The tiples are mentioned in numerous literary works
The Norato family establishes in the municipality of Chiquinquira as a manufacturer of tiples
First pictorial representations of tiples found in watercolors
The first article describing a tiple is published. There are three varieties. One with four strings, one with five strings and one with eight strings all of them paired.
Tiple continues with eight strings. The bandola adopts its pear-shaped shape.
D'Aleman method for learning to play ten and twelve strings is published.
The tiple reaches its final configuration with twelve strings
